headline.main: De Gaulle Due to Leave for Algiers Soon; Free French Deny Delay in Parley Plans

lead_paragraph: LONDON, April 1 -- General Charles de Gaulle is expected to leave Britain for North Africa soon for his conversations with General Henri Honore Giraud looking toward the ironing out of any differences that mark the unity between the French factions combatting a common enemy, it was learned today.
